After you set up service accounts, set up cloud accounts. A cloud account is a logical collection of service account/ datacenter pairings. In this way, it can be considered a “logical cloud” with bits of infrastructure from one or more other clouds. You can use cloud accounts to separate cloud resources in your organization. For example, you can separate by environment type, such as Development, Test, or Production, or by organization, such as Company A, Company B, and Company C.

  • In the Cloud Admin portal, navigate Manage > Cloud Accounts and click New to create a new service account.   
  • Enter a unique name and description for the account, and select the type of account.  
  • Click Next.
  • Select the service account you just created. The datacenters are automatically populated.
  • Select the datacenters you want to include in this cloud account. 
  • Click Save
  • After desired logical datacenters are saved for cloud account, publish cloud account to consume it.

    • See Create a Cloud Account for more information.
